LINE.Text: Obsessive Compulsive Disorder (OCD) is a clinically
recognised disorder that causes intrusive, obsessional thoughts
that can only be quelled with repeated actions (compulsions).
The lesser known facts about OCD
The World Health Organisation lists OCD as
one of the top 10 most debilitating disorders.
On average, there is a 12 year delay between
the onset of OCD and treatment being received.
To learn more about OCD and to find professional support,
please visit Counselling Directory today: www.counselling-directory.org.uk
